    <section id="design">
      <h2>Platform &amp; Build Quality</h2>
      <p>We did not access the OLSP member dashboard firsthand, so we cannot describe the interface directly. The following is based on third-party walkthroughs, official sales pages, and independent review descriptions.</p>

      <h3>The Mega Live Link</h3>
      <p>The most distinctive technical feature of LPB is the Mega Live Link — an upgrade to the standard MegaLink that dynamically routes prospects into whichever live event, challenge, or funnel is currently running in the OLSP ecosystem. Rather than pointing to a static landing page, the link updates automatically as OLSP cycles through its event calendar (twice-weekly live events on Tuesdays and Saturdays, plus rotating challenge programs). The practical implication is that a single shared link remains relevant and promotional as OLSP's schedule changes, without the member needing to update links or swap out content.</p>
      <p>Account-based attribution — rather than cookie-based tracking — means that once a prospect clicks your link and creates an OLSP account, that lead is permanently associated with you. This addresses the common affiliate problem of losing commission credit when a prospect switches devices, clears cookies, or purchases weeks after their initial click. This is a vendor claim about the technical implementation; we cannot independently verify how the attribution system operates in practice.</p>

      <h3>AI Marketing Material Generator</h3>
      <p>LPB includes an AI tool that generates promotional emails, social media posts, captions, and call scripts adapted to each upcoming live event. Vendor materials claim the output is generated "in your voice." Independent reviewers note that AI-generated content tools like this genuinely reduce the time burden of content production for recurring events, though the quality of output depends on how the system is configured and how much personal context it incorporates. We could not test the generator firsthand.</p>

      <h3>Traffic Challenges and Live Action Plans</h3>
      <p>Multiple structured challenge programs — including the 30-Day Traffic Challenge, Commission Challenge, Student Challenge, and AI Twin Challenge — are cited as included with LPB. Live Premium Action Plans provide done-for-you promotional calendars for each event: what to post, when, and how to encourage attendance. These are described as particularly useful for members who need external structure to maintain a consistent promotional schedule. Whether these challenges meaningfully accelerate results depends on the member having existing channels to apply the content in.</p>

      <h3>Private Community and Leaderboard</h3>
      <p>LPB includes a private community space inside the OLSP platform — distinct from the broader public Facebook group — described as providing more targeted peer support and strategy sharing among LPB-level members. A leaderboard and points system adds competitive recognition and occasional cash prizes for top performers, which some reviewers describe as effective for engagement and motivation.</p>

      <h3>Long-Term Platform Considerations</h3>
      <p>Live Profit Builders is entirely dependent on OLSP continuing to run live events on a reliable schedule. The $1/attendee mechanic and the Mega Live Link's dynamic routing only function while OLSP is actively hosting events and maintaining the commission infrastructure. Multiple reviewers note that a 2026 compensation change removed previously available lifetime membership options and shifted the model to higher monthly and annual subscriptions — an example of how OLSP's terms can change in ways that affect what members originally paid for.</p>
