      <h3>The $1 Per Attendee Mechanic</h3>
      <p>The $1/attendee payment is the most distinctive commission feature of LPB and the one most frequently highlighted in both vendor materials and independent reviews. It works on a per-unique-person basis: if you send 50 people to a Tuesday live session and 30 show up, you reportedly earn $30 from that single event. Independent reviewers point out two important conditions: first, the attendee must be new and verified (preventing inflated numbers through fake signups), and second, the value of this mechanic scales entirely with your ability to recruit consistent, qualified traffic to the events. For someone with a warm audience of 500 who attends regularly, $1/person per session could accumulate meaningfully. For someone just starting to build an audience, it generates minimal income regardless of the tier's appeal on paper.</p>

      <h3>Lifetime Attribution</h3>
      <p>Account-level attribution — where leads are permanently associated with the referring affiliate by OLSP account rather than browser cookie — is positioned as a significant commercial advantage over standard affiliate setups. The practical benefit is that if a lead you referred signs up for free, consumes content for three months, and then buys a $997 program, you still earn the commission. How consistently this system operates in practice, and whether it is maintained reliably across system updates and compensation plan changes, could not be confirmed from independent sources.</p>

      <h3>Lead Activation Bonuses</h3>
      <p>Referred leads can reportedly earn $5 for each of their first four completed OLSP onboarding training sessions, totalling up to $20 in potential rewards for engaging with OLSP's introductory content. This mechanic is framed as a way to incentivize leads to stay active, engage with the platform, and progress through training — which in turn exposes them to higher-tier offers. The member benefits indirectly by having more engaged leads who are more likely to purchase; the $5 rewards go to the lead, not the referring member.</p>

