      <details>
        <summary>How does the $1 per attendee commission actually work?</summary>
        <p>According to vendor sales pages and independent reviewers, LPB members earn $1 for each unique, verified person they refer who attends specific OLSP live events — typically Tuesday webinars and Saturday challenge kickoff sessions. "Verified" means the attendee must be a real person linked to your referral account; there is no apparent mechanism for inflating numbers with fake accounts. The practical earning potential scales directly with how many people you can reliably send to each session. If you regularly get 50 attendees per event and events run twice weekly, that is roughly $400/month from attendance alone — but reaching that level requires an active, responsive audience. This figure is a vendor and affiliate claim; actual payouts depend on OLSP's technical verification and payout processes, which we cannot independently audit.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Is "lifetime attribution" really permanent?</summary>
        <p>Vendor materials claim that once a prospect signs up for OLSP via your Mega Live Link, all future OLSP purchases from that person are attributed to you permanently — regardless of whether months or years pass between their initial sign-up and a later purchase. This is described as account-level attribution rather than cookie-based tracking, meaning it survives device changes, browser resets, and time. We cannot independently verify how robustly this system operates in practice, whether it has been maintained consistently through OLSP's multiple relaunches and compensation plan changes, or how reliably payouts occur on backend purchases. The 2026 compensation changes that removed lifetime membership options are a reminder that attribution and commission terms can change.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Is Live Profit Builders worth it compared to staying at the Megalink level?</summary>
        <p>Multiple independent analysts phrase their answer as: yes, but only once you're consistently earning at the Megalink level. The upgrade makes financial sense if your referral volume is high enough that the 100% front-end commission and $1/attendee mechanics generate more each month than the subscription cost ($49/month or $497/year). If you're generating fewer than 50 attendees per event and a handful of front-end sales per month, the math likely doesn't support the cost. Independent reviewers who cover OLSP's upgrade ladder consistently flag premature upgrading as the most common costly mistake among OLSP members.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What happened to the $297 one-time lifetime LPB offer?</summary>
        <p>Early LPB adopters reportedly accessed lifetime membership at a one-time price of $297. One independent review from 2025 cites this pricing and notes that public pricing was later reported as "around $997." Subsequent compensation plan changes in 2026 appear to have removed lifetime membership options across OLSP tiers, shifting the model to ongoing monthly or annual subscriptions. If you encounter references to the $297 lifetime offer in older reviews or affiliate promotions, verify directly with OLSP whether this option is still available before assuming it applies to your sign-up.</p>
